Cell.Text: Yes, you were going to demonstrate your ability, were you not?
[S] A standard spell for one skilled in Destruction magic is the Firebolt. Casting one at the seal on the ground here would be sufficient.
[S] Those invested in Restoration magic find Healing Hands to be essential. Can you cast it on me? That would prove your skill.
[S] The Fear spell has saved the life of many an Illusion mage. If you could cast it on the seal here on the ground, that would prove your skill.
[S] The Flame Atronach is a vital companion for anyone relying on Conjuration. Summoning one here would certainly show your skill.
[S] The Mage Light spell is useful to any mage, not just those specializing in Alteration. Can you cast one on the seal on the ground?
It would seem that you have yet to reach a level of skill that the College would find valuable, so I'm afraid I can't allow you to join at this time.

[S] Unfortunately, one needs to be able to cast at least Apprentice level spells in any school of magic before being allowed to join the College. | And thus, you're not skilled enough to be a candidate. I'm afraid we're not interested.

Cell.Text: [S] S|Welcome to the College of Winterhold. I am Faralda, one of the senior Wizards here. | I trust you found your journey to Winterhold not entirely unpleasant. | Now, I must advise you that if your only purpose in being here is to complain, you would be far better off speaking with the Jarl of Winterhold. | If, however, you seek something more, I will be happy to assist you.
Is there some way I can assist you?

Cell.Text: Oh, forgive me. | Most who arrive here do so because they have heard of the College beforehand. | This is the College of Winterhold, a safe haven for mages in Skyrim. A place of wisdom and arcane knowledge.

Node.Caption: MG01FaraldaInitResponse1: What is this place?

Cell.Text: I am here to assist those seeking the wisdom of the College. | And if, in the process, my presence helps to deter those who might seek to do harm, so be it. | The more important question is: why are you here?

Node.Caption: MG01FaraldaInitResponse3: Why are you out here?

Cell.Text: [S] It is no great secret that we have been unjustly blamed for a great many things over the years. | The good people of Skyrim on occasion would rather pass judgment than attempt to understand what we do here. | Thus we must take certain precautions in order to secure our safety.

Node.Caption: MG01FaraldaInitResponse2: Why would I want to complain about the College?

Cell.Text: Perhaps. But what is it you expect to find within?

Cell.Text: [S] I see. That power certainly exists, I assure you. Wield it faithfully, and few can withstand you.
